HEADWORD: Solano
<hw>So*la"no</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[Sp., fr. L. <ets>solanus</ets>
(sc. <ets>ventus</ets>), from <ets>sol</ets> the sun.]</ety> <def>A hot,
oppressive wind which sometimes blows in the Mediterranean, particularly
on the eastern coast of Spain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

